1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,400
Welcome to OpenClaw Installation Tutorial.
In this video, we'll install OpenClaw on
DigitalOcean step by step.

2
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:12,400
Step 1: Go to digitalocean.com and click
Sign Up. Enter your email and create a

3
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:13,599
or
or GitHub.

4
00:00:13,599 --> 00:00:19,600
Step 2: Verify your email. Open your inbox
and click the verification link from
DigitalOcean.

5
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,800
Step 3: Add a payment method. Click
Billing, then Payment Methods, then Add

6
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,000
connect
connect PayPal.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,399
The basic server costs $6 per month. You
can cancel anytime.

8
00:00:30,399 --> 00:00:38,399
Step 4: Create a droplet. Click the green
Create button in the top right, then
select Droplets from the menu.

9
00:00:38,399 --> 00:00:46,399
Step 5: Choose Ubuntu 22.04 LTS as your
operating system. LTS means Long Term
Support - the most stable version.

10
00:00:46,399 --> 00:00:56,799
Step 6: Select the 12 dollar per month
plan with 2 GB RAM, 1 CPU, and 50 GB SSD.
This gives you room for multiple agents.

11
00:00:56,799 --> 00:01:04,399
Step 7: Choose a data center close to you.
Europe: London or Frankfurt. USA: New York
or San Francisco.

12
00:01:04,399 --> 00:01:10,399
Step 8: Select Password authentication and
create a strong password. Write it down
somewhere safe!

13
00:01:10,399 --> 00:01:15,199
Step 9: Name your droplet. Use something
memorable like openclaw-bot or
my-ai-assistant.

14
00:01:15,199 --> 00:01:21,199
Step 10: Click Create Droplet and wait 30
to 60 seconds while it sets up.

15
00:01:21,199 --> 00:01:27,199
Step 11: Copy your server's IP address. It
looks like 138.68.161.145. Click the copy
icon.

16
00:01:27,199 --> 00:01:34,799
Step 12: Open Terminal on Mac or Command
Prompt on Windows. Type: ssh root@ then
paste your IP address.

17
00:01:34,799 --> 00:01:42,399
Step 13: Type yes when asked about
fingerprint, then enter your password. You
won't see characters as you type.

18
00:01:42,399 --> 00:01:49,199
Step 14: Update system packages. Run: apt
update && apt upgrade -y. Wait 1 to 3
minutes.

19
00:01:49,199 --> 00:01:55,599
Step 15: Install Node.js. Run: curl -fsSL
https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x |
bash - then apt install -y nodejs

20
00:01:55,599 --> 00:02:00,399
Step 16: Verify Node installation. Run:
node --version. You should see v20.x.x

21
00:02:00,399 --> 00:02:06,799
Step 17: Install OpenClaw. Run: npm
install -g openclaw. Wait 1 to 2 minutes
for installation.

22
00:02:06,799 --> 00:02:12,799
Step 18: Start OpenClaw setup. Run:
openclaw gateway start. You'll be asked
several configuration questions.

23
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:18,399
Choose anthropic as your model provider
and enter your Anthropic API key from
console.anthropic.com

24
00:02:18,399 --> 00:02:24,399
Step 19: Connect WhatsApp. A QR code will
appear. Open WhatsApp on your phone, tap

25
00:02:24,399 --> 00:02:25,599
a
a Device.

26
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:31,199
Scan the QR code on your computer screen
and wait for the Connected message.

27
00:02:31,199 --> 00:02:37,199
Congratulations! OpenClaw is now running
24/7. Send a WhatsApp message to test your
AI assistant.

28
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:42,799
For help and documentation, visit
openclaw.ai or join the Discord community.
Thanks for watching!
